lecture rodin and his american admirers events at stanford lecture rodin and his american admirers facebook twitter email print add to calendar auguste rodin the most famous sculptor of his day not only appealed to sophisticated american collectors but also had a profound influence on american artists beginning in the 1890s and persisting for decades after rodin's death in 1917 this exhibition is the first to examine the scope of this influence antoinette le normand romain directeur general de l institut national d histoire de l art paris and former curator at the musee rodin paris discusses the american art critics collectors and museum exhibitions that brought rodin's work to the united states when wednesday october 5 2011 6 00 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading international arts contact 723 3469 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 285 28575 more info last modified september 22 2011
